---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { STATS } from '../data/repos';
---

<Base
  title="About - Methodology, Scoring Rubric & Dataset Generation"
  description="How the GitHub Risk Atlas dataset was generated: 3,873 repositories scored by Claude Opus 4.7 (max thinking mode) in 40-repo batches across 4 parallel streaming sessions. Includes the full 6-tier severity rubric, calibration anchors, heuristics, and limitations."
  keywords="claude opus methodology, AI security scoring, repository severity rubric, max thinking mode, batched streaming, security research methodology, dataset generation, tier classification, vulnerability scoring"
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-10">About the Dataset</h1>

    <div class="space-y-10" style="color:#8b949e; line-height:1.8;">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" style="color:#e6edf3;">
          What is this?
        </h2>
        <p>
          GitHub Risk Atlas is an AI-generated severity ranking of <strong
            style="color:#e6edf3;"
            >{STATS.total.toLocaleString()} leaked GitHub-internal repositories</strong
          >. Each repository has been scored from 0–100 on how dangerous its
          source code would be to <em>GitHub.com customers</em> if read by a sophisticated
          attacker - i.e., how much it would help them steal customer data.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" style="color:#e6edf3;">
          Scoring methodology
        </h2>
        <p>
          Every repository was scored by <strong style="color:#e6edf3;"
            >Claude Opus 4.7</strong
          > running in <strong style="color:#e6edf3;"
            >maximum thinking mode</strong
          > (<code
            class="px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs"
            style="background:#161a22;color:#a29bfe;">--effort max</code
          >). The model was given:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 list-disc list-inside">
          <li>A detailed 6-tier severity rubric</li>
          <li>
            ~30 calibration anchors (e.g. <code style="color:#ff2d55;"
              >github - 100 S</code
            >, <code style="color:#ff6b35;">octovault - 99 S</code>, <code
              style="color:#a29bfe;">mona-sans - 5 E</code
            >)
          </li>
          <li>Heuristics for common naming patterns</li>
          <li>The repo name, archive size in bytes, and parent org</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4">
          For each verdict the model returned: <code style="color:#26de81;"
            >score</code
          >, <code style="color:#26de81;">tier</code>, <code
            style="color:#26de81;">category</code
          >, and <code style="color:#26de81;">rationale</code> - enforced by a JSON
          schema at the API level.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" style="color:#e6edf3;">
          Processing pipeline
        </h2>
        <div
          class="rounded-xl p-5 space-y-3 text-sm font-mono"
          style="background:#111318;border:1px solid #21262d;"
        >
          <div>
            <span style="color:#ff2d55;">1.</span> Parse <code>ls -la</code> dump
            - <code>repos.tsv</code> (3,874 entries)
          </div>
          <div>
            <span style="color:#ff6b35;">2.</span>
            <code>score_repos_stream_parallel.py</code> - 4 workers, batch=40
          </div>
          <div>
            <span style="color:#f7b731;">3.</span> Each batch: one stdin line - one
            JSON array of 40 verdicts
          </div>
          <div>
            <span style="color:#26de81;">4.</span> Per-worker session reset every
            20 batches (~800 repos)
          </div>
          <div>
            <span style="color:#45aaf2;">5.</span> Atomic fsync append to <code
              >scores.jsonl</code
            > per batch
          </div>
          <div>
            <span style="color:#a29bfe;">6.</span> Rate-limit detection: parse reset
            time, sleep until unlock
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-4 gap-4 mt-6">
          {
            [
              ['3,873', 'Repos scored'],
              ['19.3 min', 'Total runtime'],
              ['0', 'Failures'],
              ['~$147', 'Added cost (batched)'],
            ].map(([v, l]) => (
              <div
                class="rounded-lg p-4 text-center"
                style="background:#111318;border:1px solid #21262d;">
                <div class="text-2xl font-bold mb-1" style="color:#ff2d55;">
                  {v}
                </div>
                <div class="text-xs" style="color:#8b949e;">
                  {l}
                </div>
              </div>
            ))
          }
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" style="color:#e6edf3;">
          Tier definitions
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          {
            (
              [
                [
                  'S',
                  '95-100',
                  '#ff2d55',
                  'Crown Jewels',
                  'Auth daemons, secret vaults, octocerts, token scanning, Rails monolith, JIT access provisioning.',
                ],
                [
                  'A',
                  '85-94',
                  '#ff6b35',
                  'Customer Data',
                  'Billing, support tickets, audit logs, DMCA/law enforcement, DSR, package registries, runner admin.',
                ],
                [
                  'B',
                  '70-84',
                  '#f7b731',
                  'Core Infra',
                  'Network, DNS, Kubernetes, hosted compute, git replication, log pipelines, service mesh.',
                ],
                [
                  'C',
                  '50-69',
                  '#26de81',
                  'Internal Tools',
                  'Hubber tooling, Copilot subsystems, chatops, feature-flag platform.',
                ],
                [
                  'D',
                  '25-49',
                  '#45aaf2',
                  'Build & Docs',
                  'Build tooling, dashboards, internal docs, employee tools with no sensitive data.',
                ],
                [
                  'E',
                  '1-24',
                  '#a29bfe',
                  'Low Risk',
                  'Marketing, branding, fonts, demos, deprecated, personal scratch repos.',
                ],
              ] as const
            ).map(([t, band, col, label, desc]) => (
              <div
                class="flex gap-4 p-4 rounded-lg"
                style={`background:#111318;border-left:3px solid ${col};`}>
                <div
                  class="font-black text-2xl w-6 shrink-0"
                  style={`color:${col};`}>
                  {t}
                </div>
                <div>
                  <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-1">
                    <span class="font-semibold text-sm" style="color:#e6edf3;">
                      {label}
                    </span>
                    <span
                      class="text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
                      style={`background:${col}22;color:${col};`}>
                      {band}
                    </span>
                  </div>
                  <p class="text-sm">{desc}</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            ))
          }
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" style="color:#e6edf3;">
          Limitations
        </h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2 list-disc list-inside text-sm">
          <li>
            Scores are based on <strong style="color:#e6edf3;"
              >repository names and archive sizes only</strong
            > - no code was read.
          </li>
          <li>
            Claude's reasoning is probabilistic; any individual score may be
            miscalibrated.
          </li>
          <li>
            Ambiguous 3-letter acronyms and codenames default to mid-tier
            (40–60).
          </li>
          <li>
            Scores reflect threat to <em>GitHub.com customers</em>, not GitHub
            the company's operational security.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section
        class="rounded-xl p-5"
        style="background:rgba(255,45,85,0.05);border:1px solid rgba(255,45,85,0.2);"
      >
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3" style="color:#ff2d55;">
          ⚠ Legal disclaimer
        </h2>
        <p class="text-sm">
          This dataset and visualisation are provided for <strong
            style="color:#e6edf3;"
            >educational and security research purposes only</strong
          >. The scores represent AI-generated inferences from repository names.
          No source code was accessed or redistributed. If you are a GitHub
          employee or security researcher, please follow responsible disclosure
          procedures.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
